The paper proposes a novel reward function for reinforcement learning in robotic tasks, leveraging physical priors in the form of a time-to-reach (TTR) function computed from an approximate system dynamics model. This involves both machine learning (reinforcement learning) and robotics (system dynamics), which suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel reward function for reinforcement learning, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 

cs.RO (Robotics): The paper deals with robotic tasks and system dynamics, which suggests that it could belong to the robotics sub-category. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper leverages physical priors in the form of a time-to-reach (TTR) function computed from an approximate system dynamics model, which suggests that it could belong to the systems and control sub-category. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel reward function for reinforcement learning, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not deal explicitly with computer vision, it is possible that the robotic tasks involve visual perception, which could place it under the computer vision and pattern recognition sub-category.
